Class AlertDispatchDAO

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.ambari.server.orm.dao.AlertDispatchDAO

  • public class AlertDispatchDAO
extends Object
    The AlertDispatchDAO class manages the AlertTargetEntity, AlertGroupEntity, and the associations between them.

      • findGroupsByDefinition

        public List<AlertGroupEntity> findGroupsByDefinition(AlertDefinitionEntity definitionEntity)
        Gets all of the AlertGroupEntity instances that include the specified alert definition. Service default groups will also be returned.
        Parameters:
        definitionEntity - the definition that the group must include (not null).
        Returns:
        all alert groups that have an association with the specified definition and the definition's service default group or empty list if none exist (never null).

      • findDefaultServiceGroup

        Gets the default group for the specified cluster and service.
        Parameters:
        clusterId - the cluster that the group belongs to
        serviceName - the name of the service (not null).
        Returns:
        the default group, or null if the service name is not valid for an installed service; otherwise null should not be possible.

      • createNotices

        public List<AlertNoticeEntity> createNotices(List<AlertNoticeEntity> entities)
        Creates new alert notices using the EntityManager.merge(Object) method to ensure that the associated AlertTargetEntity instances are also updated.

        The method returns the newly managed entities as the ones passed in will not be managed.

        Parameters:
        entities - the targets to create (not null).

      • removeNoticeByDefinitionId

        public void removeNoticeByDefinitionId(long definitionId)
        Removes notifications for the specified alert definition ID. This will invoke EntityManager.clear() when completed since the JPQL statement will remove entries without going through the EM.
        Parameters:
        definitionId - the ID of the definition to remove.
